window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>FNH Audio presents an unabridged reading of H. Beam Piper's classic and much-loved science fiction novel <i>Little Fuzzy</i>. </p><p>Jack Holloway lives a solitary life in a wilderness of the planet Zarathustra. When a strange intelligent animal walks into his life from out of the forest everything is set to change. </p><p>The animal that he names 'Little Fuzzy' seems sapient and that threatens the charter of the company that owns the planet. With the company profits threatened, there's a lot riding on the sapience/non-sapience of Little Fuzzy and his fellows. Jack realises that both his life and that of Little Fuzzy are in danger. </p>"; 
